<div class="tip_number">TIP 195</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            If you have a fever and belly discomfort soon after you have given birth to a baby, it may indicate that you have a serious infection of the womb, which could spread rapidly. Heavy bleeding is also a possible warning signal of a life-threatening hemorrhage.
        </div>

</div>
